  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "What are the characteristic laboratory findings in primary hypothyroidism?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Elevated TSH, low T4 levels"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Elevated TSH, low T3 levels"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Elevated TSH, elevated T4 levels"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Low TSH, low T4 levels"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 0,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct Answer: A) Elevated TSH, low T4 levels </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation: </strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The characteristic laboratory findings in primary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8d4d1904791692777189941782330d\">hypothyroidism</span> are <strong>elevated </strong>thyroid-stimulating hormone<strong> (TSH)</strong> levels and l<strong>ow free </strong>thyroxine <strong>(T4)</strong> levels.</li>\n\t<li>This is because, in<strong> primary hypothyroidism</strong>, the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"799202e6fe16927772009a1501b0a8\">thyroid</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4744bb90c21692777188c8957f9faa\">gland</span> fails to produce sufficient <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"799202e6fe16927772009a1501b0a8\">thyroid</span> hormones, leading to decreased <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a1c9a7400e1692777203b61723d426\">feedback inhibition</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b775f0c475169277719593c573f6ff\">pituitary</span> gland, which in turn increases TSH production to try to stimulate the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"799202e6fe16927772009a1501b0a8\">thyroid</span> gland.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><strong>Primary vs Secondary Hypothyroidism:</strong></p>\n\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:721px\">\n\t<tbody>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Feature</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Primary Hypothyroidism</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:1px solid black; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Secondary Hypothyroidism</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Definition</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Thyroid <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4744bb90c21692777188c8957f9faa\">gland</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3662597407169277718640a12868f5\">dysfunction</span> leads to inadequate <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"799202e6fe16927772009a1501b0a8\">thyroid</span> hormone production</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Pituitary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3662597407169277718640a12868f5\">dysfunction</span> leads to insufficient TSH secretion</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Causes</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Autoimmune (Hashimoto's thyroiditis)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Iatrogenic (e.g., post-thyroidectomy, radiation)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Iodine deficiency</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Medications (e.g., amiodarone, lithium)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Infiltrative diseases (e.g., sarcoidosis)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Food <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"30e693d8521692777188a5ea13201b\">goitrogen</span> → Cabbage, cassava.</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pituitary tumors</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Pituitary surgery or radiation</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Sheehan’s syndrome</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Trauma</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Genetic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b775f0c475169277719593c573f6ff\">pituitary</span> hormone deficiencies</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Non-obstetric cause of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b775f0c475169277719593c573f6ff\">pituitary</span> damage called Simmonds's disease (AVM, tumor, HTN)</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Sarcoidosis</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Hemochromatosis</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Lab</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>TSH - ↑;</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Free T3/T4 - ↓</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>TSH - Normal or ↓;</p>\n\n\t\t\t<p>Free T3/T4 - ↓<strong> (Option D)</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Clinical Features</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Fatigue, weight gain, cold intolerance</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Dry skin, hair loss</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Bradycardia, constipation</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Myxedema (puffy face, non-pitting edema)</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<ul>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Similar to primary hypothyroidism</li>\n\t\t\t\t<li>Other <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b775f0c475169277719593c573f6ff\">pituitary</span> hormone deficiencies (e.g., low cortisol, low LH/FSH)</li>\n\t\t\t</ul>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t\t<tr>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:1px solid black; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p><strong>Treatment</strong></p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Levothyroxine (T4) replacement with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b5bd69c9791692777186a40f45ffb6\">dosage</span> based on TSH levels</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t\t<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid black; border-left:none; border-right:1px solid black; border-top:none; vertical-align:top\">\n\t\t\t<p>Levothyroxine (T4) replacement, but monitored by free T4 levels (since TSH is unreliable)</p>\n\t\t\t</td>\n\t\t</tr>\n\t</tbody>\n</table>\n\n<p><strong>Elevated TSH, low T3 levels (Option B): </strong>While low T3 levels can occur in primary hypothyroidism, T4 levels are more commonly measured and are more indicative of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"799202e6fe16927772009a1501b0a8\">thyroid</span> function. Low T3 alone is not specific enough to diagnose primary <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8d4d1904791692777189941782330d\">hypothyroidism</span> without considering T4 levels​</p>\n\n<p><strong>Elevated TSH, elevated T4 levels (Option C): </strong>This combination is not characteristic of primary hypothyroidism. Elevated TSH with elevated T4 levels might indicate resistance to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"799202e6fe16927772009a1501b0a8\">thyroid</span> hormone or a rare TSH-secreting <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b775f0c475169277719593c573f6ff\">pituitary</span> adenoma, but not primary hypothyroidism​</p>",
