    {
      "text": "Among the given options, which condition is expected to exhibit the greatest levels of ACTH and cortisol?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "Early morning"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Normal individuals with dexamethasone administration"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Addison's disease"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Cushing's disease"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer: (Option D) Cushing's disease</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation: </strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>Cushing’s disease:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>It is a condition characterized by the overproduction of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55fd11666f1692777180e80135bda8\">ACTH</span> by a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b775f0c475169277719593c573f6ff\">pituitary</span> tumor (adenoma).</li>\n\t<li>This excessive <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55fd11666f1692777180e80135bda8\">ACTH</span> production leads to increased <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7f3792072b1692777199fd8e2c4f59\">stimulation</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f955f012f716927771801d01e7d163\">adrenal</span> glands, causing them to produce and release excessive amounts of cortisol, a stress hormone.</li>\n\t<li>Therefore, both <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55fd11666f1692777180e80135bda8\">ACTH</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1698cefc83169277718522e3f5fd61\">cortisol</span> levels are elevated in Cushing's disease.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Corticosteroid feedback mechanism</strong></p>\n\n<p><img alt=\"PHY243\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"11823\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"May2025\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/AzLSW6Oo1D4uMXGsX1LG1746434654.png\" /></p>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Circadian rhythm: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e127a25c621692777186ed98a403f9\">Diurnal</span> pattern with peak in morning and low in evening, independent of external factors <strong>(Option A ruled out)</strong></li>\n\t<li>The <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f955f012f716927771801d01e7d163\">adrenal</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"cab8787ce916927771852a7e72f34d\">cortex</span> atrophies and becomes unresponsive to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55fd11666f1692777180e80135bda8\">ACTH</span> for about six months after a prolonged treatment with steroids. <strong>(Option B ruled out)</strong></li>\n\t<li>Adrenal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"80feaae4b31692777190ea1ba3fc25\">insufficiency</span> is precipitated as a result.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p> </p>\n\n<p><strong>Addison's disease (Option C): </strong>It is characterized by a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"209b85faf71692777185767d43e3bd\">deficiency</span> of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1698cefc83169277718522e3f5fd61\">cortisol</span> production due to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f955f012f716927771801d01e7d163\">adrenal</span> insufficiency. In this condition, both <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55fd11666f1692777180e80135bda8\">ACTH</span> and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1698cefc83169277718522e3f5fd61\">cortisol</span> levels are decreased. <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"55fd11666f1692777180e80135bda8\">ACTH</span> levels are elevated as a <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8c77461be01692777184e67e678209\">compensatory</span> mechanism to stimulate the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f955f012f716927771801d01e7d163\">adrenal</span> glands, but the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f955f012f716927771801d01e7d163\">adrenal</span> glands are unable to produce sufficient cortisol.</p>",
