      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 0,
          "text": "24 hours after ovulation"
        },
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "24 hours after delivery"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "REM sleep"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "After running four 1 hours"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<p><strong>Correct answer: (Option B) </strong>24 hours after delivery</p>\n\n<p><strong>Explanation:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>Prolactin is secreted by the mother’s <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1ba6a9cfe11692777181950edd7a6d\">anterior</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b775f0c475169277719593c573f6ff\">pituitary</span> gland</li>\n\t<li>its concentration in blood rises steadily from the fifth week of pregnancy until birth of the baby (10 to 20 times the normal nonpregnant level)</li>\n\t<li>Prolactin levels fall after delivery and the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"923af580cf16927771829606bce2a7\">basal</span> levels are low in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3d885759d516927771966b84bfa470\">postpartum</span> period</li>\n\t<li>Episodic rise is required for subsequent <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4abd8094e51692777191b1eb073735\">lactation</span> and maintenance in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"3d885759d516927771966b84bfa470\">postpartum</span> period, which happens during each act of suckling.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><img alt=\"OG234\" data-author=\"\" data-hash=\"11824\" data-license=\"\" data-source=\"\" data-tags=\"May2025\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/aOBbup9g7FIPYsk8vF9U1746434810.png\" /></p>",
